## Auth-T1 Backend RBAC — Register and login endpoint tests
**Status:** in_progress
**Test File:** `backend/src/rbac/api.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-D1, Auth-P1.1

### Verification Summary (Quinn — run-tests)

Reviewed `backend/src/rbac/api.rs`. The `register()` handler EXISTS at lines 399-440 with `POST /api/auth/register` route. Login handler EXISTS with identical credential validation. Tests below exercise both endpoints via oneshot requests against the full `rbac_api_routes()` router.

### Test Cases

| ID | Description | Expected |
|----|-------------|----------|
| TC-T1.1 | Register valid user | 201 + JWT + roles=["editor"] |
| TC-T1.2 | Register empty username | 400 |
| TC-T1.3 | Register empty password | 400 |
| TC-T1.4 | Register short password | 400 |
| TC-T1.5 | Register duplicate username | 409 |
| TC-T1.6 | Login with correct credentials | 200 + JWT |
| TC-T1.7 | Login with wrong password | 401 |
| TC-T1.8 | Login with nonexistent user | 401 |
| TC-T1.9 | Login empty fields | 400 |

### Coverage Matrix

| Auth-D1 Requirement | Test |
|---------------------|------|
| Register validates non-empty username/password | TC-T1.2, TC-T1.3, TC-T1.9 |
| Register validates password >= 4 chars | TC-T1.4 |
| Register checks username uniqueness | TC-T1.5 |
| Register creates user with "editor" role | TC-T1.1 |
| Register returns JWT token on success | TC-T1.1 |
| Login with correct credentials returns JWT | TC-T1.6 |
| Login with wrong password returns 401 | TC-T1.7 |
| Login with nonexistent user returns 401 | TC-T1.8 |

