## Auth-T1 Backend RBAC Registration — Register endpoint validates and creates users
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/rbac/api.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-D1, Auth-P1.1

### Verification Against Source (Quinn — run-tests)

Reviewed `backend/src/rbac/api.rs`. The `create_user()` admin handler already implements identical validation logic to what the design spec requires for `register()`. Tests below verify both the admin `create_user` endpoint and the planned public `register` endpoint. Once `register()` is added per Auth-P1.1, the same test pattern applies with `/api/auth/register` instead of `/api/admin/users`.


### Test Cases

#### TC-T1.1: Create user with valid username/password returns 201 and user object

```
Given: RbacState with in-memory DB and JWT secret "test-secret"
When:  POST /api/admin/users with {"username": "testuser", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 201, body contains {id, username: "testuser", roles: []}
And:   User exists in DB with username "testuser"
```

#### TC-T1.2: Create user with empty username returns 400

```
Given: RbacState with in-memory DB
When:  POST /api/admin/users with {"username": "", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Username and password required"
```

#### TC-T1.3: Create user with empty password returns 400

```
Given: RbacState with in-memory DB
When:  POST /api/admin/users with {"username": "testuser", "password": ""}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Username and password required"
```

#### TC-T1.4: Create user with short password (< 4 chars) returns 400

```
Given: RbacState with in-memory DB
When:  POST /api/admin/users with {"username": "testuser", "password": "abc"}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Password must be at least 4 characters"
```

#### TC-T1.5: Create user with duplicate username returns 409

```
Given: RbacState with user "testuser" already created
When:  POST /api/admin/users with {"username": "testuser", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 409, body contains "Username already exists"
```

### Rust Test Code (to be added to `backend/src/rbac/api.rs`)

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use crate::rbac::RbacState;
    use crate::rbac::middleware::RbacMiddlewareState;
    use axum::body::Body;
    use axum::http::{Request, StatusCode};
    use tower::ServiceExt;

    fn create_test_app() -> Router {
        let state = RbacState::new_in_memory("test-secret").unwrap();
        let mw_state = RbacMiddlewareState {
            db: state.db.clone(),
            jwt_secret: state.jwt_secret.clone(),
        };
        // Mount only the user creation route for testing
        Router::new()
            .route("/api/admin/users", post(create_user))
            .with_state(mw_state)
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_create_user_valid() {
        let app = create_test_app();
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CREATED);
        let body = axum::body::to_bytes(resp.into_body(), 4096).await.unwrap();
        let data: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&body).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(data["username"], "testuser");
        assert!(data["id"].is_number());
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_create_user_empty_username() {
        let app = create_test_app();
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
        let body = axum::body::to_bytes(resp.into_body(), 4096).await.unwrap();
        let data: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&body).unwrap();
        assert!(data["error"].as_str().unwrap().contains("required"));
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_create_user_empty_password() {
        let app = create_test_app();
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":""}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_create_user_short_password() {
        let app = create_test_app();
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"abc"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
        let body = axum::body::to_bytes(resp.into_body(), 4096).await.unwrap();
        let data: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&body).unwrap();
        assert!(data["error"].as_str().unwrap().contains("4 characters"));
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_create_user_duplicate_username() {
        let app = create_test_app();
        // First creation succeeds
        let resp = app
            .clone()
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CREATED);
        // Second creation fails
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/admin/users")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"different"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CONFLICT);
        let body = axum::body::to_bytes(resp.into_body(), 4096).await.unwrap();
        let data: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&body).unwrap();
        assert!(data["error"].as_str().unwrap().contains("already exists"));
    }
}
```

### Coverage Matrix

| Auth-D1 Requirement | Test |
|---------------------|------|
| Register validates non-empty username/password | TC-T1.2, TC-T1.3 |
| Register validates password >= 4 chars | TC-T1.4 |
| Register checks username uniqueness | TC-T1.5 |
| Register creates user with "editor" role | TC-T1.1 (verify roles when register() implemented) |
| Register returns JWT token on success | N/A — register() not yet implemented |
| Register returns 201 Created | TC-T1.1 |

## Auth-T1 Backend RBAC Registration — Register endpoint validates and creates users
**Status:** ready
**Test File:** `backend/src/rbac/api.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-D1, Auth-P1.1

### Verification Summary (Quinn — run-tests)

The `register()` handler does NOT yet exist in `backend/src/rbac/api.rs`. The existing file has `login()`, `me()`, `list_users()`, `create_user()`, `delete_user()` but no `register()` endpoint. The design (Auth-D1 §1) specifies adding a `POST /api/auth/register` route. These tests are ready for implementation once the coder adds the register handler.

### Test Cases

#### TC-T1.1: Register with valid username/password returns 201 and JWT
```
Given: RbacState with in-memory DB and JWT secret "test-secret"
When:  POST /api/auth/register with {"username": "testuser", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 201, body contains {token, user_id, username: "testuser", roles: ["editor"]}
And:   User exists in DB with username "testuser"
And:   User has "editor" role assigned
```

#### TC-T1.2: Register with empty username returns 400
```
When:  POST /api/auth/register with {"username": "", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Username and password required"
```

#### TC-T1.3: Register with empty password returns 400
```
When:  POST /api/auth/register with {"username": "testuser", "password": ""}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Username and password required"
```

#### TC-T1.4: Register with short password (< 4 chars) returns 400
```
When:  POST /api/auth/register with {"username": "testuser", "password": "abc"}
Then:  Response status 400, body contains "Password must be at least 4 characters"
```

#### TC-T1.5: Register with duplicate username returns 409
```
Given: User "testuser" already created
When:  POST /api/auth/register with {"username": "testuser", "password": "pass1234"}
Then:  Response status 409, body contains "Username already exists"
```

### Rust Test Code

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod register_tests {
    use super::*;
    use crate::rbac::RbacState;
    use axum::body::Body;
    use axum::http::{Request, StatusCode};
    use tower::ServiceExt;

    async fn create_test_app() -> Router {
        let state = RbacState::new_in_memory("test-secret").unwrap();
        let mw_state = RbacMiddlewareState {
            db: state.db.clone(),
            jwt_secret: state.jwt_secret.clone(),
        };
        rbac_api_routes().with_state(mw_state)
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_register_valid_user() {
        let app = create_test_app().await;
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CREATED);
        let body = axum::body::to_bytes(resp.into_body(), 1024).await.unwrap();
        let data: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&body).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(data["username"], "testuser");
        assert!(data["token"].is_string());
        assert!(data["roles"].as_array().unwrap().iter().any(|r| r == "editor"));
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_register_empty_username() {
        let app = create_test_app().await;
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_register_empty_password() {
        let app = create_test_app().await;
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":""}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_register_short_password() {
        let app = create_test_app().await;
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"abc"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::BAD_REQUEST);
    }

    #[tokio::test]
    async fn test_register_duplicate_username() {
        let app = create_test_app().await;
        // First registration succeeds
        let resp = app
            .clone()
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"pass1234"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CREATED);
        // Second registration with same username fails
        let resp = app
            .oneshot(
                Request::builder()
                    .method("POST")
                    .uri("/api/auth/register")
                    .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
                    .body(Body::from(r#"{"username":"testuser","password":"different"}"#))
                    .unwrap(),
            )
            .await
            .unwrap();
        assert_eq!(resp.status(), StatusCode::CONFLICT);
    }
}
```

### Coverage Matrix

| Auth-D1 Requirement | Test |
|---------------------|------|
| Register validates non-empty username/password | TC-T1.2, TC-T1.3 |
| Register validates password >= 4 chars | TC-T1.4 |
| Register checks username uniqueness | TC-T1.5 |
| Register creates user with "editor" role | TC-T1.1 |
| Register returns JWT token on success | TC-T1.1 |
| Register returns 201 Created | TC-T1.1 |

### Implementation Gap

**BLOCKER**: The `register()` handler and `POST /api/auth/register` route do not exist in `backend/src/rbac/api.rs`. The `rbac_api_routes()` function needs to be updated to include this route. Coder must implement per Auth-D1 §1.

