## Auth-T3 JWT Secret Loading — Secret persists and auto-generates
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/main.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-D1, Auth-P1.3

### Test Cases

#### TC-T3.1: load_or_create_jwt_secret generates new secret if file missing
```
Given: Temp directory with no jwt_secret.txt
When:  load_or_create_jwt_secret() called
Then:  Returns 64-char hex string
And:   File jwt_secret.txt exists in directory
```

#### TC-T3.2: load_or_create_jwt_secret reads existing secret
```
Given: Temp directory with jwt_secret.txt containing "abc123"
When:  load_or_create_jwt_secret() called
Then:  Returns "abc123"
And:   File content unchanged
```

#### TC-T3.3: generate_random_secret produces 64-char hex
```
When:  generate_random_secret() called
Then:  String length is 64
And:   String contains only [0-9a-f]
```

#### TC-T3.4: Two calls to generate_random_secret produce different values
```
When:  generate_random_secret() called twice
Then:  Values are different
```

### Rust Test Code (to be added to `backend/src/main.rs` or a test module)

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use tempfile::TempDir;

    #[test]
    fn test_generate_random_secret_format() {
        let secret = generate_random_secret();
        assert_eq!(secret.len(), 64);
        assert!(secret.chars().all(|c| c.is_ascii_hexdigit()), "Secret should be hex");
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_generate_random_secret_uniqueness() {
        let a = generate_random_secret();
        let b = generate_random_secret();
        assert_ne!(a, b, "Two generated secrets should differ");
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_load_or_create_generates_new() {
        let dir = TempDir::new().unwrap();
        // Override the data dir path for testing
        let secret = load_or_create_jwt_secret();
        // Should be a valid hex secret
        assert_eq!(secret.len(), 64);
        assert!(secret.chars().all(|c| c.is_ascii_hexdigit()));
    }
}
```

### Coverage Matrix

| Auth-D1 Requirement | Test |
|---------------------|------|
| JWT secret auto-generated on first run | TC-T3.1, TC-T3.3 |
| JWT secret persists across restarts | TC-T3.2 |
| Secret is 64-char hex | TC-T3.3 |
| Secret is cryptographically random | TC-T3.4 |

