## Auth-T4 Frontend App Auth Guard — LoginView shown when unauthenticated, main app when authenticated
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `frontend/src/App.vue` (component test)
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-D1, Auth-P1.5, Auth-P1.6

### Verification Summary (Quinn — run-tests)

**NOT YET IMPLEMENTED.** The auth guard in `App.vue` (v-if="!isAuthenticated") and `LoginView.vue` do not exist yet. Per Auth-P1.5 and Auth-P1.6, these are new files. These tests are acceptance criteria for the coder.

### Test Cases

#### TC-T4.1: Unauthenticated state shows LoginView
```
Given: useAuth().isAuthenticated === false
When:  App.vue renders
Then:  LoginView component is visible
And:   Main app content (.autoforge-app) is NOT rendered
```

#### TC-T4.2: Authenticated state shows main app
```
Given: useAuth().isAuthenticated === true
  And: useAuth().user.username === "admin"
When:  App.vue renders
Then:  Main app content (.autoforge-app) is visible
And:   LoginView is NOT rendered
```

#### TC-T4.3: Auth success event switches to main app
```
Given: App renders with LoginView (unauthenticated)
When:  LoginView emits "auth-success"
Then:  Main app content appears
And:   LoginView is hidden
```

#### TC-T4.4: User menu shows username initial and logout button
```
Given: Authenticated with username "admin"
When:  App.vue nav rail renders
Then:  .user-avatar shows "A"
And:   Logout button (LogOut icon) is visible
```

#### TC-T4.5: Logout returns to LoginView
```
Given: Authenticated state
When:  User clicks logout button
Then:  useAuth().logout() is called
And:   LoginView appears
```

#### TC-T4.6: Page refresh preserves session via stored token
```
Given: localStorage has valid "autoforge_jwt" token
When:  App mounts (fresh page load)
Then:  validateStoredToken() is called
And:   If valid, main app shows directly (no login flash)
```

#### TC-T4.7: i18n keys exist for all auth strings
```
Given: en.json and zh.json loaded
Then:  Both have: auth.username, auth.password, auth.login, auth.register,
       auth.loading, auth.noAccount, auth.hasAccount, auth.logout, auth.defaultHint
```

### Coverage Matrix

| Auth-D1 Requirement | Test |
|---------------------|------|
| LoginView shown when unauthenticated | TC-T4.1 |
| Main app shown when authenticated | TC-T4.2 |
| auth-success event transitions to app | TC-T4.3 |
| User menu with avatar + logout | TC-T4.4, TC-T4.5 |
| Token validation on mount | TC-T4.6 |
| i18n keys for auth UI | TC-T4.7 |
| 401 clears auth and shows LoginView | Auth-T3 TC-T3.8 |

### Implementation Gap

**BLOCKER**: Auth guard in App.vue and LoginView.vue do not exist. Coder must implement per Auth-P1.5 and Auth-P1.6.

